<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-02-14T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-02-14T06:00:00-05:00" n="717" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1153 St 2/40: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-14T11:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">February 14,
                                        1928—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 14—9:25
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>41. Reference to the Department’s 14, February 1, and 15, February 2,
                            both to Madrid.<note n="22" xml:id="d717fn22">Latter not printed.</note>
                            Following consultations with Mr. Blair en route from Madrid to London
                            and back from there, where he was encouraged by developments, the
                            Spanish oil situation has been informally <pb facs="0961" n="851" xml:id="pg_851"/> discussed by this Embassy with the French Foreign
                            Office. The desirability of the French Embassy in London aiding in
                            bringing the British Government to favor concerted action was especially
                            suggested. I refer to the Department’s No. 2607 of February 2.<note n="23" xml:id="d717fn23">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
